NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# DO NOT COMMIT SECRETS TO SOURCE CONTROL
# Key Rotation Policy:
# - Service Role Keys MUST NOT be included in any client-side bundle or committed to git.
# - If a Supabase Service Role Key is exposed, it must be IMMEDIATELY rotated via the Supabase Dashboard (Settings -> API).
# - Application environments (Staging/Production) must use environment variables injected securely by the hosting provider (e.g., Vercel, AWS Secrets Manager).
# - Conduct an exposure sweep using git-filter-repo post-rotation to scrub historical commits.
